10 November 2009Government will hold Ministerial Cluster Media Briefings on the implementation of the Government Programme of Action as announced in June by President Jacob Zuma.The briefings will take place at the Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town. There will be a video link up to Room 153, Union Buildings, PretoriaBriefings schedule:Tuesday, 10 November 200912h00-12h30: Human DevelopmentNB: As part of the cluster briefing, the Minister of Health will do an extended briefing on the NHI and HIV/AIDS.Wednesday, 11 November 200912h00-13h30: International Cooperation, Trade and SecurityThursday, 12 November 200912h00-13h30: Governance &amp; AdministrationFriday, 13 November 200912h00-13h30: Justice, Crime Prevention and Security NB: The briefing date for the Infrastructure Development Cluster will be announced at a later stage.Enquiries Bongiwe Gambu Cell: 082 714 9463Colin Cruywagen Cell: 082 377 9916Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)